The paper discusses the ethical and legal questions surrounding Lethal Autonomous Weapons and proposes programming values and principles of conduct into the machines' control. This suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also employs mathematical logic and theoretical computer science, indicating a possible fit with categories such as ethics in computing (cs.ET), software engineering (cs.SE), and machine learning (cs.LG).
